    <item>
      <title>The Developer AI Journal: Bridging the Pedagogical Gap in GenAI</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/beyond-declaration/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/beyond-declaration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;project-overview&#34;&gt;Project Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Generative AI becomes a ubiquitous co-pilot in software development, the challenge for educators shifts from preventing its use to &lt;strong&gt;integrating it professionally&lt;/strong&gt;. The &lt;em&gt;Developer AI Journal&lt;/em&gt; (or Prompt Logger) is a research-led tool designed at the &lt;strong&gt;University of Sydney&lt;/strong&gt; to transform AI usage from a hidden shortcut into a transparent engineering artifact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project aims to answer a critical research question: &lt;em&gt;How can we foster &amp;lsquo;Human-in-the-loop&amp;rsquo; accountability while using LLMs in project-based learning?&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;key-capabilities&#34;&gt;Key Capabilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-Platform Ingestion:&lt;/strong&gt; Automated fetching and parsing of shared chat links from Gemini, and Microsoft Copilot to ensure high data fidelity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reflective Taxonomy:&lt;/strong&gt; A structured framework requiring students to categorise AI accuracy and justify their manual interventions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional Audit Trail:&lt;/strong&gt; Generates version-controlled logs that serve as &amp;lsquo;Evidence of Work&amp;rsquo; for group projects and individual assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pedagogical Analytics:&lt;/strong&gt; Real-time monitoring of student &amp;lsquo;Evaluation Confidence&amp;rsquo; vs. &amp;lsquo;AI Accuracy&amp;rsquo; to detect skill gaps and over-reliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
